Nigerian singer, songwriter Tiwa Savage recently took to her Insta Stories to share a message for companies which are allegedly owing her millions. “I might have to call out these companies that owe me millions,” she says.
“If you no get, say you no get… no dey use style yan something else. I know how much revenue my brand has generated your brand, don’t even try it,” she added.
Tiwa concluded: “You better SAN WO OLU. Na we get Lagos ooo. Check the contract”. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-951462 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories-598x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1280" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories-598x598.jpg 598w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories-1152x1152.jpg 1152w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories-100x100.jpg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories-200x200.jpg 200w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories-487x487.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories-974x974.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories-240x240.jpg 240w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories-480x480.jpg 480w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories-600x600.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Tiwa-Savage-instastories.jpg 1472w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> This is coming after her amicable departure from Mavin Records and her subsequent songwriting deal with Sony/ATV Music Publishing. 